IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: Spencer Chamber of Commerce endeavors to promote civic, economic, industrial, and agricultural development. The association is committed to fostering an environment which creates jobs, enhances economic opportunities and improves the quality of life for the Spencer area. By pooling the talents and resources of the entire community, this voluntary organization of business and industry works together to improve the quality of life for the Spencer area.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Form 990 is presented to the Board of Directors for review
before submission to the IRS. Once approved by the Board
the Form 990 is filed.
All public documents are available for viewing in the
Chamber office upon request.
The salary of key employees is determined by the
Executive Director using comparable salaries for the
position as well as adjustments for experience in
similar positions.
The independant accounted was selected using a bid process.
All Chamber Members in the accounting field were provided
an opportunity to bid for the job of completing the Review
and Compilation. Bids were reviewed for cost and ability
of the firm to provide information in a timely fashion.
A vote was taken to award the contract to the winner.
The organization has members consisting of local businesses
who provide membership dues for the operation of the Chamber.
Members are nominated for the Board of Directors by a
committee consisting of current Board Directors. The
list of nominees is then provided to all members for
vote with highest vote count becoming Directors.
Each year employees and board members are required to read
review and sign the conflict of interest policy. The interested
persons are also responsible to report any changes in this
situation during the year.
